name: Main Street Bar & Grille
directions: Two in the back straight from the door

name: DIT conservatory of music
directions: When you go to the front door turn left straight away and you’ll see the gender neutral toilets, all the other bathrooms are also trans friendly
comment: It’s a music school but they don’t ask who you are, worst you’ll get is a bad look

name: Bon Appetea
directions: Two restrooms specifically marked as any gender.
comment: Trans friendly business.

name: University Service/Nelson's Auto World
directions: Bathroom is in the back past the drink coolers.
comment:
Hours: M-F 7am-9pm, Sat 9am-5pm, Sun 10-6

Sign says nobody under 18 allowed without parent, unsure if that's enforced.

Re: accessiblily. The bathroom door is definitely big enough for a wheelchair but there are no handrails near the toilet.

The employees are super nice!

name: Harlan Hatcher Graduate Library
directions: Hatcher South, sixth floor across from the elevators/by Special Collections

name: Del Taco
directions: On the right side of the building next to the door
comment: Need to be unlocked by an employee

name: Potbelly Sandwich Shop
directions: 2 single stall gender neutral restrooms in back of store

name: Troy Public Library
directions: Near the circulation desk.
comment: Ask for a key at the circulation desk.  Only restroom B has a changing table.

name: Coffee traders
directions: It's on the first floor right behind the stairs on the right. The doors don't have signs on them.
comment: Try not to look like you are there just to use the bathroom, it's a coffee shop.

name: Partner's Coffee Roasters
directions: In the back on the left before the courtyard

name: Friendly Neighborhood Pub
comment: Casual pub

name: Cumberland Farms
directions: In the back behind the snacks

name: Second Cup
directions: Situated at the back of the store, second door on the hallway.
comment: No need to buy anything, walk and walk out!

name: Cineworld Cinema
comment: Unisex disabled single stall.

name: The Moon Under Water
comment: Disabled bathroom, single occupancy in between the men's and women's.

name: University of Portsmouth Student Union
directions: First floor. Turn right at the top of the stairs along the mezzanine. At the end turn left through a set of double doors, turn right down the corridor through another set of double doors. The toilets are on the left.
comment: Accessible during the day just pretend you’re a student

name: Somisomi
directions: Back right corner of the store

name: Commonwealth Building
directions: First floor, up the ramp (or stairs) to the left, and down the center hallway. The bathroom is on the lefthand side of the hallway past the small phone rooms.
comment: Probably technically for tenants of the office building, but the lobby is unlocked and open to the public.

name: Save-On-Foods
directions: Through produce to the back by the fish counter.
comment: No key required

name: Turlington Hall
directions: Outside, next to the water fountain

name: Starbucks
directions: Enter the fire door with poster on right and head downstairs. Door has a code lock.
comment: You need to order something and ask for the door code from the server.

name: North Riverside Park Mall
directions: In the back of the food court, right side.

name: State Theater
directions: near women’s bathroom and stage
comment: have to pay for a ticket

name: Collegetowm Bagels
directions: pretty obvious where it is but if you can’t find it, employees would be happy to help

name: Casa dello studente
directions: Casa dello studente de lollis. Arrivati nel giardino interno dopo il cancello, vi è una scala sulla destra. Porta ad un posto autogestito, con i bagni queer.

name: Market Mall
comment: There are two gender neutral/handicap/gender neutral bathrooms here, smelly but most bathrooms usually are

name: Santinis
comment: Gendered (m/f) single person bathroom

name: Trader Joes
directions: Back right of the store as you walk in
comment: Very clean and roomy

name: Trader Joe’s
directions: Back right side of store. Clearly marked
comment: Clean

name: Barrie Community Health Centre
directions: Second floor on the left side of social work hall, accessible via elevator. Trans friendly clinic behind Huronia Urgent Care
comment: You “must” be a patient but most of the time they can’t tell if you aren’t, and if they can, the staff will understand of needing to use a safe bathroom!

name: Barrie CHC
directions: Take elevator to 2nd floor, back of social work hallway on left
comment: This is in a clinic behind the Huronia urgent care clinic. You “need” to be a patient but they won’t actually know if you aren’t 99% of the time. Trans friendly clinic and staff will understand.

name: Corazon
directions: Two gender neutral single stall locking  bathrooms between the dining areas.

name: Lord Gascoigne
directions: Left of the bar when you enter the pub - at the back near the TV

name: Costa
directions: At the back of the store

name: Shrimp N’ Stuff
directions: In the back corner next to the soda machines.
comment: Easier to enter the restaurant through the outside sitting area next to the parking lot

name: Hillsborough County courthouse
directions: On the same side as room 140

name: Market Basket
directions: In the very front of the store, by the seating, there are two gender neutral single stall restrooms.

name: Trader Joe’s
directions: Back of the store, first door in the left under the restrooms sign

name: Corner Brook Plaza Family Room
directions: Located in the same area as the gendered mall bathrooms, signs in the plaza will point you in the right direction.
comment: Has 2 toilets in single stall which can be useful for parents and children or even couples!

name: Grenfell Campus
directions: Multiple gender neutral restrooms on campus - one in the Arts and Science building across from the gym (very accessible and has changing table), two on the top floor of the Fine Arts building (not accessible and do not have changing tables), and one in the Forest Centre (unsure if accessible or if it has a changing table, but it is on the top floor of the Forest Centre).
comment: You don't need to be a student at the campus to use the restroom! Just head on in.

name: Corner Brook Public Library
directions: In the back of the library, bottom floor, by the elevators.

name: Millbrook Mall
directions: Located on the lowest level of the mall, in the same area where the gendered restrooms are located.

name: Corner Brook Public Library
directions: 2 accessible gender neutral bathrooms at the back by the elevators.

name: Corner Brook Public Library
directions: 2 accessible gender neutral bathrooms at the back by the elevators.

name: Walla Walla Clinic - Pediatrics
directions: This department currently has 4 restrooms in service, all single-stall gender-neutral & accessible. The 1 just inside the entrance also has a changing table. The others are past the reception desk & down the main hall in either direction.
comment: You're expected to be a patient or accompanying a patient.

name: Walla Walla Clinic - Podiatry, Surgery, Urology
directions: These departments share 2 restrooms, both of which are single-stall, gender-neutral; neither has a changing table. 1 is accessible. They are found their a door & past a nurses' station, so are more for patients, I think. The most public ones are back down the hall, past the main entrance & to the left of the switchboard reception booth.
comment: You're expected to be a patient or accompanying a patient.

name: Walla Walla Clinic - Laboratory
directions: This restroom is near the lab techs' station & considered 'clinical', for a patient's visit. A slightly more public restroom is located through a door to the Podiatry reception desk.
comment: You're expected to be a patient for this restroom.

name: Walla Walla Clinic - Radiology
directions: Left-hand hall facing the reception desk, first door on the right.
comment: You're expected to be a patient or accompanying a patient.

name: Walla Walla Clinic - Walk-In Clinic & Derm
directions: These 2 departments share public restrooms outside their waiting rooms, near the switchboard reception booth. Both are single-stall gender-neutral; 1 is accessible & has a changing table.
comment: You're generally expected to be a patient or accompanying a patient, but these restrooms are truly public.

name: Walla Walla Clinic - Allergy & Endocrinology
directions: These departments share a restroom near the nurses' stations which is considered 'clinical', for a patient's visit. For the public restrooms, head straight out of the waiting room, and they're on your right just past the switchboard reception booth. They're both single-stall gender-neutral. 1 is accessible & has a changing table.
comment: You're expected to be a patient or accompanying a patient, but the public restrooms are truly public.

name: Walla Walla Clinic - Internal Med & Gastro
directions: These departments share 3 restrooms, 1 of which is near a nurses' station & considered 'clinical', for a patient's visit. The other 2 face the top of the stairs on the 2nd floor & nearly face the elevator. All 3 restrooms are accessible & gender-neutral; none has a changing table.
comment: You're expected to be a patient or accompanying a patient.

name: Walla Walla Clinic - Cardio, Diag Img, IV Therapy
directions: This department has 3 restrooms, 1 of which is gender-neutral & accessible (once you reach the dept via ramps). The other 2 are single-stall gendered & inaccessible. None of them have changing tables.
comment: You're expected to be a patient or accompanying a patient.

name: Walla Walla Clinic - Women's Clinic
directions: This department has 5 restrooms, all of which are gender-neutral. 4 are near nurses' stations & considered 'clinical', for patient visits; 1 of these is accessible. The 1 at the back of the waiting room is also accessible & has a changing table.
comment: You're expected to be a patient or accompanying a patient

name: Walla Walla Clinic - Family Medicine
directions: 4 restrooms in this department, all accessible & gender-neutral. The one nearest the waiting room has a changing table & is considered the public restroom. The others are near nurses' stations & considered 'clinical', for during patient visits.
comment: You're expected to be a patient or accompanying a patient.

name: Walla Walla Clinic - Physical Therapy
directions: past the waiting room, down the hall to your right
comment: You're expected to be a patient or accompanying a patient.

name: Earthlight Books
directions: back left corner, on a short hall

name: Book & Game Co.
directions: through the back of the store into the mall-like hallway; must ask for key
comment: may be 2 stalls, but generally kept locked - so safer than average

name: Impress Salon
directions: Left back corner, past all the stations
comment: These people are LGBTQ-friendly, including to trans* folk.

name: Harvest Foods
directions: back of the store, past the produce & paper product sections

name: Burwood Brewing
directions: down a hall to the right past the bar
comment: They co-host Community Pride's monthly Queer Cheer & are welcoming and friendly.

name: Quirk Brewing
directions: front right corner, past the window & shelves of games

name: Andy's Market
directions: front left corner, past the checkstands & through the freezer section
comment: They're straight through an open doorway, in a short dark hallway.

name: Safeway (Plaza)
directions: front left corner, past the deli

name: Paw-Paw’s
directions: Far left corner through the arch way, past the kitchen, and up the ramp. Two bathrooms.
comment: They’re real nice I’m sure you can just ask to use their restroom.

name: Paw-Paw’s
directions: Left side of the building in the back through the doorway. Past the kitchen and up the ramps.
comment: They’re real nice here, I’m sure they’ll let you go to the bathroom

name: Seven Virtues Coffee Roasters on Glisan
comment: You must order something in order to be allowed to use the restroom.

name: Billy Beez
directions: Unisex family restroom upstairs
comment: Must be a paying customer here with a child. Restroom has very quiet fan (good for sensory issues) and child changing table.

name: Mustang mini mart
directions: In the back next to the soda machine

name: Jiffy Lube
directions: In the waiting area of the shop.

name: ANKORS (AIDS Network Outreach & Support Society)
directions: In the building marked "Labour Centre", the bathroom is immediately to your right when you enter.
comment:
During drop-in hours the bathroom is open to the public, you have to ask for a key from the front desk. 
Re accessibility: The bathroom is ground-level access, but there is no hand rail.

name: Bitterroot BBQ
directions: Two single room restrooms in hall to bar

name: Macleod’s fish and chips Scottish pub
directions: Near the kitchen
comment: Pride flags on chalkboard. Definitely a safe space.

name: Midtown Station
directions: Public lobby
comment: Single stall gender neutral in public lobby area.  Lobby is open 8-4

name: Nandos
directions: Upstairs past the tills
comment: You have to be paying customer

name: The Habit Burger Grill
directions: By the kitchen, 2 separate neutral bathrooms.
